[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29611245","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3928#issuecomment-29611245","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3928","id":29611245,"user":{"login":"karlitschek","id":867445,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/87ce2b4531ee1a0c32b50e0d8f049224?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f06e7098636caebfc9c30c9f52eb905df.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"87ce2b4531ee1a0c32b50e0d8f049224","url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek","html_url":"https://github.com/karlitschek","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-02t11:36:52z","updated_at":"2013-12-02t11:36:52z","body":"should be possible with a webdav fuse driver. but this is out of scope of the owncloud project. "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/30141913","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3928#issuecomment-30141913","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3928","id":30141913,"user":{"login":"deltaphi","id":2348915,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/b4a8700d62367ad5ebc1d8319e94fe24?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f82579626083f04e13acdda4748a42cdc.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"b4a8700d62367ad5ebc1d8319e94fe24","url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi","html_url":"https://github.com/deltaphi","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deltaphi/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-09t15:40:39z","updated_at":"2013-12-09t15:40:39z","body":"fuse using webdav is not actually a solution to the problem, it rather is the cause. as written in my initial post, webdav access is slow on a low-power machine. for large files, it is unusably slow.\r\n\r\nmainly what would be needed from owncloud to allow for development of such an \"owncloud fuse fs\" would be an api to access the information on how the data is arranged in an owncloud share, i.e., folders, filenames, permissions and mappings of filenames to actual files on disk.\r\n\r\nit should be sufficient to have this api in php. a \"owncloud fuse fs\" can then be implemented outside the owncloud project using this api in c (bridging to php) or purely in php (using fuse bindings). this means that metadata operations probably will not be extremely fast, however the bulk load of transporting the contents of a file can be taken off of php/the webserver."}]